body:
@TomAugspurger your summary is almost correct. Having compblib='blosc' and complevel=None results in compression, in this case complevel defaults to 9. The summary looks like:
**Master:**
- complib defined + complevel missing: compression with level set to 9
- complib defined + complevel defined: compression with level set to level
- complib missing + complevel missing: no compression 
- complib missing + complevel defined: no compression

**PR:**
- complib defined + complevel missing: No compression
- complib defined + complevel defined: compression with level set to level
- complib missing + complevel missing: no compression 
- complib missing + complevel defined: compression with zlib and level set to level

I pasted the results of my experiments on master below if anyone is interested, the relevant info is in the FILTERS tag. I added tests to cover the various combinations of missing and defined complevel and complib in my PR.

